  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response in Ethiopia: Addressing the Humanitarian Needs of Displaced Populations and Vulnerable Returnees in Gambella, Oromia, and Somali Regions and Southern Nations Nationalities and Peoples (SNNP) Regions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Natural and man-made disasters &#x2013; primarily conflict, flooding, and drought &#x2013; continue to affect Ethiopia on an increasing scale. These disasters are major drivers of displacement and have led the 2021 Humanitarian Response Plan Mid-Year Review to estimate 14.8 million people in need of humanitarian assistance across the country. The intervention aims to mitigate the risk of humanitarian crisis posed by the large scale of internal displacement responding to urgent shelter and non-food items needs of displaced populations in Gambella, Oromia, Southern Nations Nationalities and Peoples, and Somali regions.</narrative>
  </description>
